canonical:
  title: 七家嶺遇雨
  author: 崔淑精
  language: lzh
  text: 上苑花飛春事休客中何處賦登樓黃梅籬落千家暮宿麥平疇一望秋風雨五更鄕國夢江山萬里旅窓愁傷心短笛聲聲苦挑盡殘燈白盡頭
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 七家嶺遇雨
  author: 崔淑精
  language: lzh
  text: 上苑花飛春事休。客中何處賦登樓。黃梅籬落千家暮。宿麥平疇一望秋。風雨五更鄕國夢。江山萬里旅窓愁。傷心短笛聲聲苦。挑盡殘燈白盡頭。
korean:
  title: 칠가령 우우
  author: 최숙정
  language: kor
  text: |-
    상원에 꽃이 날아 봄 일이 끝났는데
    나그네 길 어느 곳에서 등루하였다는 시를 지으리
    누른 매화가 핀 울타리에는 집집마다 저물었는데
    보리가 익은 펀펀한 밭에는 볼수록 가을뿐이다
    비바람의 오경에는 고국의 꿈이요
    강과 산의 만리에는 나그네 창의 시름이다
    상하는 마음에는 짧은 젓대의 소리소리가 괴로운데
    쇠잔한 등불을 돋우어 다하기에 머리가 모두 희었더라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1430_010_1060&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Rain at Seven Family Ridge
  author: Choi Suk-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In the palace gardens, spring blossoms scatter and drift away—
    where in this traveler's journey shall I compose verses of the tower?
    Yellow plum blossoms frame the fences as dusk settles on every house,
    and across the barley fields stretching far, autumn deepens with each glance.

    In the fifth watch, as rain and wind fall, I dream of my homeland,
    while ten thousand miles of rivers and mountains weigh upon my window.
    My breaking heart—each note of the flute cuts sharper still,
    and tending the fading lamp through the night, my hair has turned to snow.
  footnotes:
    - Seven Family Ridge (七家嶺) is a geographical location, likely in the region the poet is traveling through.
    - The 'fifth watch' (五更) refers to the darkest hour before dawn, a traditional time for melancholy reflection in East Asian poetry.
    - The flute serves as both a literal instrument and a metaphor for the poet's sorrow—its mournful tones reflecting the traveler's inner desolation.
